        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 3:28PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 328 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 8 miles south of Montgomery
to 13 miles east of Many. Movement was north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Natchitoches, Montgomery, Provencal, Natchez, Robeline,
Cloutierville, Melrose, Bellwood, Chopin, Flora, Cypress, Bermuda,
Aloha, and Hagewood.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
